// Event Loop.
The Event Loop is the manager of Node.js.

Work:
Checks completed tasks
Executes callback functions
Simple Line:

Event Loop checks “Is any task finished?


// Thread Pool
Thread Pool is a group of background workers.

Work:
Handles heavy tasks
Works separately from main thread
Examples:
File reading
Database work
API calls
Simple Line:

Thread Pool does heavy work in background.

// Event Queue
Event Queue is a waiting line of tasks.
Work:
Stores completed callbacks
Waits for Event Loop
Simple Line:

Event Queue is the waiting area for tasks.

//Headers 
Headers are extra information sent with a request or response in web development.

They help the client and server understand the data.
ex:
When you open a shopping website:
Server gets product data from database
Server creates full HTML page
Browser receives ready page and displays it fast


// Server-Side Rendering :
 (SSR) means the web page is created on the server first and then sent to the browser as ready-made HTML.

