//Socket

A socket is a communication connection between two computers over a network.

 // REDIRECT = vapas home page pai bhej deta hai.  

req.url → Gives the requested route/page from the client.

req.method → Tells which HTTP method is used like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE.

req.headers → Gives extra client/browser information like content type, token, cookies, browser info.

req.body → Contains data sent by client in POST or PUT request.

req.params → Gives route parameters from URL.

req.query → Gives query values from URL.

req.socket → Gives network connection information between client and server.

//Routing Request.

Routing means checking the user request URL and sending the user to the correct page or response.

 // STREAM = In web development, streaming means sending data from server to browser piece by piece instead of waiting for the whole response to be ready.

//  SOCKET =socket mtlb actual communication kai ek traha se gate ha.. mtlb ushi se data ata ha aur ushi se jataa hai...

//  CHUNK = In web development, a chunk means a small piece of data sent from server to client.

//Reading Chunks

When big data is sent or received, it is not transferred all at once.
It is divided into small pieces called chunks.

//Buffering Chunks

A buffer is temporary memory used to store chunks before processing them.

//  Buffer = temporary storage memory

Data pehle buffer mein store hota hai, then process hota hai.

