// EVENT LOOP..
In web development, the event loop is a mechanism in JavaScript that helps the browser handle multiple tasks without freezing the webpage.

It continuously checks:

Are there any pending tasks like:
button clicks
API responses
timers (setTimeout)
user actions

If yes, it executes them one by one.

// USER REQUEST & CLIENT REQUEST..
A user request is an action made by the user (like clicking a button or opening a website), while a client request is the HTTP request sent by the browser/client to the server to get data or a webpage.

Example
User clicks Login button → User Request
Browser sends login data to server → Client Request


//THREAAD..
A thread is a small execution unit inside a program that performs a task independently, for example 
It helps the computer do multiple tasks at the same time.

Real-Life Example

Listening to music 🎵
Downloading a file 📥
Writing notes 📝

//Parsing Data
Parsing means converting data from one format into another format so that a program can understand and use it.

//Parsing Request → Reading and understanding the data sent by the client/user to the server.

//Asynchronous (Async)

Asynchronous means a task works in the background without stopping the main program.

//"Anonymous function:
An asynchronous function is a function that performs a task that may take time (like reading a file, calling an API, or accessing a database) without blocking the rest of the program.
                                 OR
Anonymous Function: A function that has no name. It is commonly used for temporary work and as a callback function when the function is needed only once.

