//. Backticks `
These are called template literals in JavaScript.
They allow you to insert variables directly inside a string.

Example:

let name = "Deepanshu";
console.log(`Hello ${name}`);

//${PORT}
$ itself has no special meaning here.
${ } is a placeholder used inside template literals.
Whatever value is stored in the variable PORT will be inserted into the string.

Example:

let PORT = 3000;
console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);

//Default Export: Exports a single main value from a file and is imported without curly braces {}.

Named Export: Exports multiple values from a file and is imported using curly braces {} with the exact exported names.


